HTML :
Hyper text markup language.
It is not a programming language.
It is used for a creating web-language.
It describe structure of web page using markup.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title> simple html document. </title>
</head>
<body>
<h1> simple html document. </h1>
</body>
</html>
<!----head= element is a container for metadata. The <head> element is placed between the <html> tag and the <body> tag


HEADING, PARAGRAPH, LINK :
HEADING TAG :
Heading are defined with <h1> to <h6> tags.
<h1></h1>
<h2></h2>
<h3></h3>
<h4></h4>
<h5></h5>
<h6></h6>
 
PARAGRAPH TAG :
<p> is used for paragraph.                                        <!-----<p></p>------>
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <p>______</p>
         </body>
         </html>


LINK :
HTML links are hyperlinks.                                        <!-----<a></a>------>
<a> is used for link.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <p><a href="url">descripter</a></p>
         </body>        
         </html>
<!----href= it maens on which page we want to ladder.---->
<!----descripter= it is used for on which address we want to nevigate.----->
ex.:- <a href="https://www.google.com"> Google </a>
      

HTML ATTRIBUTES :
Element(additional information).
It is basically in pair(name & value).
href= link are defined with <a> tag.
src= image are defined with <img> tag.
    ex.:- <img src= "img_girl.jpg">
width & height
    ex.:- <img src="img_girl.jpg" width="200" height="300">
alt= alternative text


LINE BREAK :
The HTML <br> element defines a line break.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <p>______<br>______</p>.
         </body>
         </html>


PRE TAG :
It is preformatted text.                                          <!-----<pre></pre>.----->
Width of font is fixed.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<h1>________</h1>
<pre>______</pre>
</body>
</html>                    


STYLE ATTRIBUTES :
<tag_name style= "property:value;">
ex.:- <p style= "color:green; font-size:300%; color:red;"> i am green </p>.


TEXT ALIGNMENT :
The text-align property specifies the horizontal alignment of text in an element.
<h1 style= "text-align:center;> centered heading </h1>
       
       
TEXT FORMATTING :
<b>= bold text
<strong>= important text
<i>= italic text
<em>= emphasized text
<mark>= marked text
<small>= small text
<del>= deleted text
<ins>= inserted text
<sub>= subscript text
<sup>= superscript text


QUOTATION ADDRESS :
<q> element defines a short quotation.
<html>
<body>
<p></p>
<p>_______:<q>________</q></p>
</body>
</html>


BLOCKQUOTE :
HTML <blockquote> element defines a section that is quoted from another source.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <p>_______</p>
         <blockquote cite="http://www.worldwildlife.org/who/index.html"></blockquote>
         </body>
         </html>
Browser support: opera, mozela firefox, crome, explorer.


ABBREVIATIONS :
The HTML <abbr> tag is used for indicating an abbreviation like etc., pvt., ltd.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <head>
         </head>
         <body>
         <p>_____<abbr title = "Private">pvt.</abbr></p> 
         </body>
         </html>


ADDRESS :
The <address> element identifies contact information relevant to the current site, page, document, section, or article.
The contact information can be an email address, URL, physical address, phone number, social media handle, etc.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <h1>_________</h1>
         <address> Written by <a href="mailto:webmaster@example.com">Jon Doe</a>.<br> 
         Visit us at:<br>
         Example.com<br>
         Box 564, Disneyland<br>
         USA </address>
         </body>
         </html>


BDO TAG :
The <bdo> element is used override the default directionality of text. 
It is used to display characters from languages that are read from right-to-left.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <p><bdo dir="rtl">This paragraph will go right-to-left.</bdo></p>  
         </body>
         </html>


COMMENT :
Syntax:- <!-----write your comment----->


COLOR :
HTML colors are specified using predefined color names.
It can also be specified using RGB values, HEX values, HSL values, RGBA values & HSLA values.
BACKGROUND :
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <h1 style="background-color:color_name;">color_name</h1>
         </body>
         </html>
TEXT :
Syntax:-<!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <h1 style="color:color_name;"> Text </h1>
         </body>
         </html>
BORDER :
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <body>
         <h1 style="border:2px color_name> Text </h1>
         </body>
         </html>
 
 
CSS (STYLE TAG) :
Cascading style sheet.
CSS can be added to HTML elements in 3 ways:
     1. Incline
     2. Internal
     3. External
INCLINE :
It is used to apply a unique style to a single HTML element.
An inline CSS uses the style attribute of an HTML element.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html> 
         <body>
         <h1 style="color:color_name;">This is a Blue Heading</h1>
         </body>
         </html>
INTERNAL :
An internal CSS is defined in the <head> section within a <style> element.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <head>
         <style>
         body{background-color: color_name;}         <!------we can style body,heading, paragraph,etc. in style tag.----->
         </style>
         </head>
         <body>
         <h1> Text </h1>
         <p> Text </p>                 <!------if you want to color the text then in style tag mention the h1{color:color_name;}    p{color;color_name;}----->
         </body>
         </html>
EXTERNAL :
With the help of the external style sheet you can change the look of an entire web site by changing one file.
To use external style sheet add a link to it in the <head> section of the HTML page.


CSS BORDER :
A border around the HTML element.
The type of border is: dotted, dashed, solid, double, groove, ridge, inset, outset, none, hidden.
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html> 
         <head>
         <style>
         p.name_of_border {border-style: name_of_border;}
         </style>
         </head>
         <body>
         <p class="name_o_boredr"> Text </p>
         </body>
         </html>
         
         
CSS PADDING :
It is the space between the text and the border.
For specifying the padding for each side of an element:
padding-top
padding-right
padding-bottom
padding-left
All the padding properties can have the following values:
length - specifies a padding in px, pt, cm, etc.
% - specifies a padding in % of the width of the containing element
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <head>
         <style>
         div {
         padding: 40px; border: 2px solid #4CAF50;
         }
         </style>
         </head>
         <body>
         <div> Text </div>
         </body>
         </html>
         
         
CSS MARGIN :-
It is a margin (space) around the element, outside the border.
For specifying the margin for each side of an element:
margin-top
margin-right
margin-bottom
margin-left
All the margin properties can have the following values:
auto - the browser calculates the margin
length - specifies a margin in px, pt, cm, etc.
% - specifies a margin in % of the width of the containing element
Syntax:- <!DOCTYPE html>
         <html>
         <head>
         <style>
         div {
         border: 2px color_name;
         margin-top: 150px;
         margin-bottom: 200px;
         margin-right: 250px;
         margin-left: 90px;
         background-color: color_name;
         }
         </style>
         </head>
         <body>
         <h2> Text </h2>
         <div> Text </div>
         </body>
         </html>
         
         
